The paper presents a technique for automatically detecting and fixing resource leaks in Android applications using static analysis. This involves analyzing the control flow of the application, which is a key concern in software engineering (cs.SE). The technique involves building a fix consisting of release operations, which involves program transformation (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the correctness of the fixes produced, which is a concern in computer security (cs.CR). The technique is evaluated empirically, which involves experimentation and measurement (cs.SD). Finally, the technique is designed to enhance the quality of Android applications, which is a concern in systems and control (cs.SY).
